            <title>[CAY-2505] EventBridge providers should be bound without scope</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAY-2505</link>
                <project id="12310903" key="CAY">Cayenne</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently all event bridge providers (JMS, XMPP, JGroups) are bound in default scope (i.e. as singletons). And that brakes things in case of shared &lt;tt&gt;DataRowStore&lt;/tt&gt; is disabled.&lt;br/&gt;
So they should be bound without scope and provide new instances for every request to provider.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
